erson who explained it to him who knew nothing himself may of told him that. Damage bonus, in the sense of the tag that is on ALL weapons post 25, is determined by your level and nothing else. At level 60, a lammy will have a damage bonus of 11. At level 60, a defiance will have a damage bonus of 11. It depends on your level, NOTHING ELSE. If the person who had that 5 damage bonus of Lammy also had a Definace, it would be 5 damage bonus as well.<br><br>Edit: I'd still take the Defiance over Lamentation. <p>Veteran Fulorian Cavestomper <BR>60th Warlord of Xegony<BR>Val'Kori</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufuloriancavestomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FulorianCavestomper</A> at: 2/10/02 12:08:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrendleyebite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grendl Eyebite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:17:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1783.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defiance VS Lammy!</span><hr size=1> The basic damage bonus formula for one handers is:<br>level minus 25 divided by 3<br><br>for two handers:<br>level minus 25 divided by 2<br><br>The bonus only applies to the right hand for one handers, but note that ANY weapon you inspect will show a bonus after 25th level, even a weapon you inspect that a vendor has for sale, or a weapon in your left hand. <br><br>Also note that a few months back, there was a patch that boosted the damage bonus for weapons over 40 delay, but I'm not sure what the equation for it is. My various 2 handers have the following damage bonuses:<br>Culler (37 delay): 16<br>Mithril Staff (45 delay): 21<br>Weighted Axe (150 delay): 61<br><br>but ANY one hander on me always shows a damage bonus of 9....  even a rusty dagger. <br><br>Damage bonus adds to the damage you inflict with a given weapon. Basic 'maximum' damage formula is skill plus strength divided by 100, times weapon damage rating, plus bonus damage. Average damage is usually 2 times the weapon's damage rating plus bonus damage. <br><br>So, when I wield a Lamentation, the numbers look something like this: <br>Average: 9 x 2 = 18, 18+9 = 27<br>Maximum: 210 (skill) + 209 (strength) = 419, divided by 100 = 4.19<br>4.19 times 9 (Lamentation damage) = 37.71<br>37.71 + 9 (my damage bonus [52-25=27, 27 / 3 = 9] ) = 46.71<br><br>*Edit*<br><br>And as long as we're crunching numbers, a lot of my guildmates have asked me to explain why a Lamentation is better than a Centi Longsword, or a Wurmslayer, or whatever. <br>So, lets look at the numbers:<br>We'll arbitrarily pick a time increment, lets say 100 delay points. <br>My Lamentation swings an average 27, and in 100 delay points, thats an average of <br>100 divided by 19 (Lamentation delay) = 5.2631 swings.<br>5.2631 times 27 = 142.1037 damage over 100 delay. <br><br>A Centi Longsword in my hands would look like this:<br>14 x 2 = 28, 28 + 9 = 37<br>100 divided by 27 (CLS delay) = 3.7037 swings. <br>3.7037 times 37 = 137.0369 damage over 100 delay. <br><br>Lamentation superior, right? Well, maybe not. <br>Lets say I am level 20, with 100 skill, and a 150 strength, and no bonus damage....<br><br>Now we have this:<br>Lamentation: 2 x 9 = 18, 18 x 5.2631 = 94.7358 damage over 100 delay. <br><br>Centi Longsword: 2 x 14 = 28, 28 x 3.7037 = 103.7036 damage over 100 delay. <br><br>Centi superior?  <br>Its all in the damage bonus. On a faster weapon, your damage bonus, if any, 'cycles' more often, inflicting more damage. Its complicated, but if you really want to be doing the maximum damage, down to a point or two over a minute, you're going to need to take a hard look at the numbers and see what works best for you. But as a general rule, the faster of two weapons with a similar ratio will inflict more damage over time after level 25. <br><br>And thats not even mentioning the increased taunt value on a faster weapon, and that's what we warriors are really about: taking the beating. <br><br>Class is over, sorry bout the long post. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      <p><FONT FACE="Lucida Bright"><b><CENTER>~Grendl Eyebite~</b><BR>~52 Barbarian Warrior~<BR>~Whack-A-Mole Enthusiast~<BR></CENTER></FONT></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrendleyebite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grendl Eyebite</A> at: 2/11/02 4:16:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 323<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:47:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1783.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defiance VS Lammy!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>'average' swing for me is 46.71 damage<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>The formula you are using for mean damage is not correct. Your average hit - often called the magic number on these boards - is (2*weapon damage) + bonus. The formula you are using is very close to the MAX damage formula. Your aveage hit with a lammy should be much closer to 27. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrendleyebite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grendl Eyebite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 4:14:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1783.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Defiance VS Lammy!</span><hr size=1> Well, at least once a week, I have to make an idiot of myself or I start looking for the pod....<br><br>/em bangs head mercilessly against a wall. <br><br>Correct numbers entered and recalculations made. Thx for the heads up, Wandor. <br><br>Insomniacs should not do math.<br><br>~Grendl <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=1783.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=1783.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1783.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=h